    "objective": "“to examine the population pharmacokinetics of lamotrigine in patients newly diagnosed with epilepsy and receiving oral lamotrigine monotherapy for up to 48 weeks”",
    "covariates": "Tested: WT, RAE, AGE, SEX, OC, Dose, Treatment duration Included: RACE, Treatment duration on CL",
    "observations": "The lack of weight as a covariate is surprising, as most other models show a relation of WT with Cl. The difference in CL in Asian patients was derived from only 5 asian patients, which is quite low for assessing such differences. Clearance is induced by about 15% over de course of roughly 25 weeks",
